<!-- ════ WHAT IS COMPANY FORMATION IN KUWAIT ════ -->
<section id="details" style="background:#fff;padding:76px 24px;position:relative;overflow:hidden;">
  <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:repeating-linear-gradient(135deg,transparent,transparent 48px,rgba(56,178,172,0.04) 48px,rgba(56,178,172,0.04) 49px);pointer-events:none;z-index:0;"></div>

  <div class="sec-inner split-grid" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.2fr 1fr;gap:52px;align-items:center;">
    <div>
      <p style="color:#2D3748;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:0.75rem;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:12px;">
        <span style="display:inline-block;width:28px;height:1px;background:#2D3748;"></span>Overview
      </p>
      <h2 style="font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.2rem);font-weight:900;color:#1A202C;line-height:1.2;margin:0 0 18px;">What is Company Formation in Kuwait?</h2>
      <p style="color:#4B5563;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;">
        Company formation in Kuwait is the process of registering a legal entity that can conduct business activities in the country. There are different types of companies that can be formed in Kuwait, depending on the nature and size of the business, the number and nationality of the shareholders, and the level of liability and taxation.
      </p>
      <p style="color:#4B5563;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;">
        The most common type of company that foreigners can form in Kuwait is a Limited Liability Company (LLC), also known as a With Limited Liability Company (WLL) in Kuwait. An LLC is a separate legal entity that provides limited liability protection to its shareholders, who are not liable for the debts or obligations of the company beyond their share capital. An LLC is also exempt from income tax in Kuwait, except for foreign shareholders who are subject to a 15% withholding tax on their profits.
      </p>
      <div style="background:#F0FFFE;border:1px solid #B2F5EA;border-radius:12px;padding:18px;">
        <p style="color:#4B5563;font-size:1rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">
          However, an LLC requires at least one Kuwaiti partner who owns at least 51% of the shares, according to Article 23 of the Kuwaiti Commercial Code. This means that foreigners cannot have full ownership or control over their business in Kuwait unless they operate in certain sectors that allow up to 100% foreign ownership under Law Number 8 on Regulating Foreign Capital Direct Investment in Kuwait.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div style="position:relative;border-radius:20px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);">
        <img src="/images/kuwait-flag.webp" alt="Company formation Kuwait" style="width:100%;height:440px;object-fit:cover;display:block;" />
